.TH VIZIER-BUILD 1 "UNRELEASED" "Vizier" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
vizier-build \- build and patch orchestration commands
.SH BUILD REFERENCE
.nf
Create build sessions and execute them through queued materialize/approve/review/merge jobs

Usage: vizier build [OPTIONS] [COMMAND]

Commands:
  execute  Execute a succeeded build session by queueing materialize/approve/review/merge jobs

Options:
  -f, --file <PATH>                  Path to the build file (TOML or JSON)
  -v, --verbose...                   Increase stderr verbosity (`-v` = info, `-vv` = debug); quiet wins over verbose, and output still honors TTY/--no-ansi gating
      --name <NAME>                  Optional stable build id override (letters/numbers/dashes, no leading '.', no '/')
  -q, --quiet                        Silence progress/history; only errors and explicit output (help/outcome) remain
  -d, --debug                        Enable debug logging (alias for -vv; kept for parity with older workflows)
      --no-ansi                      Disable ANSI control sequences even on TTYs (non-TTY is always plain); useful for CI/log scrapers
  -l, --load-session <LOAD_SESSION>  Load session context from `.vizier/sessions/<id>/session.json` before running
  -n, --no-session                   Skip writing session logs (for compliance-sensitive runs)
      --agent <SELECTOR>             Agent selector to run for assistant-backed commands (e.g., `codex`, `gemini`, or a custom shim name). Overrides config for this run
  -C, --config-file <CONFIG_FILE>    Config file to load (supports JSON or TOML); bypasses the normal global+repo layering
  -P, --push                         Push the current branch to origin after mutating git history (approve/merge/save flows)
      --no-commit                    Leave changes staged/dirty instead of committing automatically (`[workflow] no_commit_default` sets the default posture)
      --follow                       Attach to a scheduled job and stream logs until completion (requires MESSAGE/--file when stdin would otherwise be read)
  -h, --help                         Print help
  -V, --version                      Print version
.fi
.SH PATCH REFERENCE
.nf
Queue one or more intent/spec files in deterministic order using build execution pipelines

Usage: vizier patch [OPTIONS] <FILE>...

Arguments:
  <FILE>...  One or more intent/spec files to process in the exact CLI order

Options:
      --pipeline <PIPELINE>          Override the default phase pipeline for each file (default: approve-review-merge) [possible values: approve, approve-review, approve-review-merge]
  -v, --verbose...                   Increase stderr verbosity (`-v` = info, `-vv` = debug); quiet wins over verbose, and output still honors TTY/--no-ansi gating
  -q, --quiet                        Silence progress/history; only errors and explicit output (help/outcome) remain
      --target <BRANCH>              Override the merge target branch used by downstream phases
  -d, --debug                        Enable debug logging (alias for -vv; kept for parity with older workflows)
      --resume                       Resume from prior execution state by enqueueing only missing/non-terminal phases
      --no-ansi                      Disable ANSI control sequences even on TTYs (non-TTY is always plain); useful for CI/log scrapers
  -y, --yes                          Skip interactive confirmation prompts
      --after <JOB_ID>               Wait for one or more predecessor jobs before the first queued patch root starts
  -l, --load-session <LOAD_SESSION>  Load session context from `.vizier/sessions/<id>/session.json` before running
  -n, --no-session                   Skip writing session logs (for compliance-sensitive runs)
      --agent <SELECTOR>             Agent selector to run for assistant-backed commands (e.g., `codex`, `gemini`, or a custom shim name). Overrides config for this run
  -C, --config-file <CONFIG_FILE>    Config file to load (supports JSON or TOML); bypasses the normal global+repo layering
  -P, --push                         Push the current branch to origin after mutating git history (approve/merge/save flows)
      --no-commit                    Leave changes staged/dirty instead of committing automatically (`[workflow] no_commit_default` sets the default posture)
      --follow                       Attach to a scheduled job and stream logs until completion (requires MESSAGE/--file when stdin would otherwise be read)
  -h, --help                         Print help
  -V, --version                      Print version
.fi
